dismissalComment.html: so 74 it is! Soft dismissal to end the innings and fitting too when you look at the scorecard, he was trying to work it to the on side, leading edge popped up to cover

headshotImage.caption: Phillip Hughes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Phillip Hughes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: the captain's sharp at slip! A circumspect Hughes walks back, Kulasekara angled it across the left-hander from over the wicket, it was full and moving away, Hughes was looking to run it down to third man and that would have been okay had there been just one slip, Jayawardene moved quickly to his left at second slip and took it low

headshotImage.caption: David Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: David Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Appeal for a caught behind and Hussey has been given not out, and SL are reviewing it. This one nips back in from outside off, Hussey was looking to cut, there was a sound as the ball passes the bat and Perera takes it well diving to his left. Kettleborough didn't pick it up and Mahela wanted it reviewed, Hot Spot showed a thin inside edge

Bailey pads up and Aus have lost two in two! Kulasekara's inswing is really causing trouble to the right-handers, moved back in and Bailey was forward and across to shoulder arms, the ball hits his pads and he was in front of the off stump

The middle stump has been pushed back and Kulasekara has picked up his fourth! He gets the Australian captain, Kula's inswing to the right-handers is causing havoc at the Gabba, Clarke was looking to play down the ground but left a gap between pad and bat, the ball sneaked through and knocked back the stump

headshotImage.caption: Moises Henriques player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Moises Henriques player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Five for the road for Kula and Australia are a trainwreck at the Gabba! That inswing again, needs no further mention, Henriques gets across and he too is bowled through the gate, hits the top of the stumps

the attrition rate gets worse for the hosts! Malinga gets this one to move towards middle stump from over the wicket, Johnson tries to work it away to the on side, the ball hits his pad and then heads towards middle stump, almost through the gate

Now even that score of 70 looks days away! Soft dismissal for Wade, this was pitched up and moving away from the left-hander, he tries to steer it square on the off side but ends up spooning a catch to backward point

headshotImage.caption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: caught behind! This could have sent back even a genuine batsman, Malinga gets this one to move away from the right-hander, McKay was caught at the crease and couldn't move across to cover the line, thin edge and Perera takes it

headshotImage.longCaption: Shaminda Eranga player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: David Warner c Eranga b Mathews 4 (11b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 36.36

dismissalComment.html: Warner slaps it straight to mid-off! This wasn't exactly Mathews' best bal, it was short and wide and deserving to be hit, Warner chased it and flat-batted it towards mid-off, Eranga jumped and cupped it over his head and nearly fluffed it as the ball slipped out of his hand as he tried to throw it away in celebration. The umpires had a look for a few seconds but were convinced he was in control. Nervy moment for Eranga

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023
headshotImage.longCaption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

dismissalComment.html: Sri Lanka have lost two in two and the hosts are smiling again! Mathews gets a brute of a delivery from Johnson, it was short of a length and gaining on his body, he had barely enough time to make up his mend whether to duck or fend it off, took his eyes off the ball and the top edge lobbed tamely to Starc who ran across from short midwicket

....and Australia sneak in another! Strac bowls this full and wide and across the left-hander, Tharanga pushes at it away from the body, thick outside edge to Clarke who falls low to his left at first slip

another throw away! Mahela sighs in the dressing room, this was on a good length and Jeevan shaped to pull in front of square, gets a top edge, slips and falls at the crease and McKay ensures he takes it at midwicket

headshotImage.longCaption: Kusal Perera player page headshot cutout 2021

commentTextItems.html: finishes it off with a boundary! They really huffed and puffed getting there didn't they? Bowls that full outside off and he opens the face of the bat and steers it past gully

commentPostTextItems.html: Clarke: "A horrible day. Probably should have bowled first. But if you bat like that in any conditions, you will lose. Our defence let us down more than anything. No excuse for the way we performed. Shot selection was poor. I understand the public wants us playing consistently. Honestly, if we played like that (today) then the public wouldn't want to see us playing at all. Our bowlers did a good job."

Clarke was clearly peeved with himself for the way he and his team played. Nice to see a captain be so honest about his own team. Not all captains in world cricket today can say 'yes we messed up real bad.' You have to admire Clarke for that.
Nuwan Kulasekara is the Man of the Match. A no-brainer. Sometime later, see if you guys can catch the highlights on Youtube or TV and see how he squared everyone up with his inswing.

Sri Lanka are 2-1 up ahead of the 4th ODI, They won't be so happy about the way they chased this, but that's a worry for another day. They can afford to savour 74 all out today. Great performance in the field.
Thanks for your company. Thanks for the mails. The 4th match is on the 20th, same time, at the SCG. Cheers!

goes for another slog and he misses this one completely, what's happening guys?

Dropped by Warner of all people would you believe this! Kushal tried to chip it over the on side and got a thick top edge, swirled towards cover and Warner was under it, miles up in the air and he fluffed it

commentPostTextItems.html: Andy: "Selectors, please. If Chanidimal is fit for the next match please keep Kushal Perera in the side and drop Tharanga. Players like Kushal is the future and should be given as many chances as possible to flourish."

dismissalText.commentary: David Warner c Eranga b Mathews 4 (11b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 36.36

dismissalComment.html: Warner slaps it straight to mid-off! This wasn't exactly Mathews' best bal, it was short and wide and deserving to be hit, Warner chased it and flat-batted it towards mid-off, Eranga jumped and cupped it over his head and nearly fluffed it as the ball slipped out of his hand as he tried to throw it away in celebration. The umpires had a look for a few seconds but were convinced he was in control. Nervy moment for Eranga

dismissalText.commentary: Phillip Hughes c Jayawardene b Kulasekara 3 (14b 0x4 0x6 23m) SR: 21.42

dismissalComment.html: the captain's sharp at slip! A circumspect Hughes walks back, Kulasekara angled it across the left-hander from over the wicket, it was full and moving away, Hughes was looking to run it down to third man and that would have been okay had there been just one slip, Jayawardene moved quickly to his left at second slip and took it low

dismissalText.commentary: David Hussey c †MDKJ Perera b Kulasekara 4 (6b 1x4 0x6 9m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: Appeal for a caught behind and Hussey has been given not out, and SL are reviewing it. This one nips back in from outside off, Hussey was looking to cut, there was a sound as the ball passes the bat and Perera takes it well diving to his left. Kettleborough didn't pick it up and Mahela wanted it reviewed, Hot Spot showed a thin inside edge

dismissalText.commentary: George Bailey lbw b Kulasekara 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Bailey pads up and Aus have lost two in two! Kulasekara's inswing is really causing trouble to the right-handers, moved back in and Bailey was forward and across to shoulder arms, the ball hits his pads and he was in front of the off stump

dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke b Kulasekara 9 (26b 1x4 0x6 44m) SR: 34.61

dismissalComment.html: The middle stump has been pushed back and Kulasekara has picked up his fourth! He gets the Australian captain, Kula's inswing to the right-handers is causing havoc at the Gabba, Clarke was looking to play down the ground but left a gap between pad and bat, the ball sneaked through and knocked back the stump

dismissalText.commentary: Moises Henriques b Kulasekara 2 (2b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Five for the road for Kula and Australia are a trainwreck at the Gabba! That inswing again, needs no further mention, Henriques gets across and he too is bowled through the gate, hits the top of the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Mitchell Johnson b Malinga 2 (16b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 12.5

dismissalComment.html: the attrition rate gets worse for the hosts! Malinga gets this one to move towards middle stump from over the wicket, Johnson tries to work it away to the on side, the ball hits his pad and then heads towards middle stump, almost through the gate

dismissalText.commentary: Matthew Wade c Dilshan b Malinga 8 (21b 0x4 0x6 48m) SR: 38.09

dismissalComment.html: Now even that score of 70 looks days away! Soft dismissal for Wade, this was pitched up and moving away from the left-hander, he tries to steer it square on the off side but ends up spooning a catch to backward point

dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene c Warner b McKay 1 (5b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 20

dismissalComment.html: Warner takes a brilliant one at backward point! That will lift Australia's sagging spirits, this was short and wide outside off, Mahela was on his toes to cut that, moved quickly to Warner's left and he threw himself to his left and took it with both hands, sharp reflexes

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Clarke b Johnson 22 (33b 3x4 0x6 44m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: strange old Dilshan innings comes to an end in a freakish manner, Johnson bowled it on a good length outside off, Dilshan was looking to shoulder arms but the ball straightened and took the outside edge to first slip, he wasn't offering a shot

dismissalText.commentary: Lahiru Thirimanne c Warner b Johnson 7 (24b 1x4 0x6 48m) SR: 29.16

dismissalComment.html: take that! Warner's seeing it like a foot ball! Johnson fires that on a good length and Thirimanne makes room and tries to bash that past point, Warner's reflexes are sharp, catches it with both hands, made that look easy

dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews c Starc b Johnson 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Sri Lanka have lost two in two and the hosts are smiling again! Mathews gets a brute of a delivery from Johnson, it was short of a length and gaining on his body, he had barely enough time to make up his mend whether to duck or fend it off, took his eyes off the ball and the top edge lobbed tamely to Starc who ran across from short midwicket

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga c Clarke b Starc 12 (15b 2x4 0x6 20m) SR: 80

dismissalComment.html: ....and Australia sneak in another! Strac bowls this full and wide and across the left-hander, Tharanga pushes at it away from the body, thick outside edge to Clarke who falls low to his left at first slip
